<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="472" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1594,2015]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1666,1691]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[330,518,1666,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Hypotelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevis">
<emphasis box="[330,518,1666,1691]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Hypotelus laevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be easily distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1106,1220,1666,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Hypotelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1106,1220,1666,1691]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Hypotelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a pair of broad and pointed frontal processes on the head, as long as scape (
<figureCitation box="[817,909,1702,1727]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 19" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1913,1935]" captionTargetBox="[216,1355,230,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,157,1945]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 19. Habitus, dorsal view. 9, Hypotelus insulanus, syntype, male; 10, H. praecox, lectotype, female; 11, H. scheerpeltzi sp. nov., holotype, male; 12, H. testaceus, syntype, male; 13, H. melanodelta sp. nov., holotype, female; 14, H. castaneus sp. nov., holotype, male; 15, H. brevitarsus sp. nov., holotype, male; 16, H. corniculatus sp. nov., holotype, female; 17, H. marginatus, syntype, male; 18, H. laevis, male; 19, H. andinus. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803652/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Figs. 18</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[921,992,1703,1727]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 24" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1116,1138]" captionTargetBox="[308,1288,231,1075]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[234,1353,193,1095]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 24. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. 20, Hypotelus castaneus sp. nov., male; 21, H. castaneus sp. nov., female; 22, H. corniculatus sp. nov., female; 23, H. laevis, male; 24, H. laevis, female. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803654/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">23–24</figureCitation>
